[49m[38;5;10m+       1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 13.5: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simple, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 13.5. It shows one way you could translate clinical pathway graph modeling into working Python code using boto3, Neptune's openCypher endpoint, and DynamoDB for patient state tracking. It is not production-ready. There's no connection pooling, no retry logic beyond boto3 defaults, no input validation, no proper error handling. Think of it as the sketchpad version: useful for understanding how clinical pathways become traversable graphs and how patient state advances through them, not something you'd deploy to a hospital CDS system on Monday morning. A starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a few supporting libraries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 requests
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs permissions for Neptune (`neptune-db:ReadDataViaQuery`, `neptune-db:WriteDataViaQuery` scoped to your cluster), DynamoDB (`dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:UpdateItem`, `dynamodb:Query`), S3 (`s3:PutObject` for pathway version storage), and network access to Neptune from within your VPC.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Neptune doesn't use IAM for query authentication by default (it uses VPC-level network isolation). If you've enabled IAM auth on your cluster, you'll need to sign requests with SigV4. This example assumes VPC network access without IAM auth for simplicity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before we get to the steps, here's the configuration that drives the pipeline. These constants define the Neptune endpoint, the pathway graph schema, and the condition evaluation logic that determines when a patient advances along a pathway.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import requests
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Configure logging. In production, use structured JSON logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # for CloudWatch Logs Insights queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # PHI Safety: Patient pathway state references patient identifiers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Never log patient IDs alongside clinical data in the same log entry.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune cluster endpoint. Use the writer endpoint for loads,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # reader endpoint for queries. In production, separate these.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune runs inside your VPC. This code must execute from within
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # the same VPC (Lambda in VPC, EC2, ECS, etc.) to reach it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_WRITER_ENDPOINT = "your-neptune-cluster.cluster-xxxxxxxxxxxx.us-east-1.neptune.amazonaws.com"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_READER_ENDPOINT = "your-neptune-cluster.cluster-ro-xxxxxxxxxxxx.us-east-1.neptune.amazonaws.com"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_PORT = 8182
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune exposes openCypher queries via HTTPS POST to this path.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_WRITER_URL = f"https://{NEPTUNE_WRITER_ENDPOINT}:{NEPTUNE_PORT}/openCypher"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_READER_URL = f"https://{NEPTUNE_READER_ENDPOINT}:{NEPTUNE_PORT}/openCypher"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # DynamoDB table for patient pathway state.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Partition key: patient_id (String)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Sort key: pathway_id (String)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PATIENT_STATE_TABLE = "patient-pathway-state"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # S3 bucket for versioned pathway definitions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PATHWAY_VERSIONS_BUCKET = "clinical-pathways"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # AWS region for all service calls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m AWS_REGION = "us-east-1"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # How often the overdue-check Lambda runs (minutes).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Used for logging context, not for scheduling (EventBridge handles that).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m OVERDUE_CHECK_INTERVAL_MINUTES = 15
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Valid node types in the pathway graph.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Each type has different semantics for traversal and completion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NODE_TYPES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "start",                # Entry point. Exactly one per pathway.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment",           # Clinician evaluates something (e.g., calculate CURB-65).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "order",               # Place a clinical order (labs, meds, imaging).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "decision_point",      # Branch based on conditions. Must have 2+ outgoing edges.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "milestone",           # Marker for progress tracking (no action required).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "discharge_criterion", # Terminal node. Patient meets discharge criteria.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Valid edge types connecting pathway nodes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m EDGE_TYPES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "sequential",      # Must happen in order. No conditions beyond completion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "conditional",     # Taken only if conditions are met. Exclusive with siblings.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "time_gated",      # Available only after elapsed time threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "parallel_start",  # Begins a parallel branch (multiple paths active).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "parallel_join",   # Waits for all parallel branches to complete.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Valid condition types for edge evaluation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m CONDITION_TYPES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "lab_value",            # Compare a lab result against a threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "vital_sign",           # Compare a vital sign against a threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "elapsed_time",         # Hours since entering current node.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment_complete",  # A specific assessment has been documented.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "order_placed",         # A specific order has been placed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "allergy_check",        # Patient has (or doesn't have) a specific allergy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "diagnosis_present",    # Patient has a specific diagnosis on their problem list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Comparison operators for conditions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m OPERATORS = ["gt", "gte", "lt", "lte", "eq", "neq", "exists", "not_exists"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Model the Pathway as a Graph
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this the pathway schema definition. Before any Neptune queries happen, you need a structured representation of a clinical pathway that can be loaded into the graph database. This step defines the data structures and builds a sample pneumonia pathway.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def build_sample_pneumonia_pathway() -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Build a simplified community-acquired pneumonia pathway as a graph structure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is a teaching example. A real pathway would have 30-50 nodes with
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     complex branching. This one has 8 nodes to keep the traversal logic clear.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The pathway models:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Initial assessment and severity scoring
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Branching based on severity (mild vs. moderate/severe)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Antibiotic initiation with time constraint
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. 48-hour reassessment with step-down or escalation branches
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     5. Discharge criteria
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         A dictionary with 'nodes' and 'edges' lists ready for Neptune loading.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     pathway_id = "community-acquired-pneumonia"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     pathway_version = 3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     nodes = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "id": f"{pathway_id}-v{pathway_version}-start",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "pathway_id": pathway_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "pathway_version": pathway_version,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "node_type": "start",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "name": "Patient Presents with Suspected Pneumonia",
